You need to register your Named Commands as the FIRST thing in Robot Container. They are not in your code.
public RobotContainer() {

            NamedCommands.registerCommand("Elevator Arm To Coral Station",
                            cf.setSetpointCommand(Setpoint.kCoralStation));

            NamedCommands.registerCommand("Elevator Arm To Coral L4",
                            cf.setSetpointCommand(Setpoint.kLevel4));

The String names have to be the same as called out in Path Planner and then the Command specified. The video is pretty clear on that from 1:15:30

This error is almost certainly your problem.

at frc.robot.RobotContainer.(RobotContainer.java:68)
at frc.robot.Robot.(Robot.java:29)
at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:370)
at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.lambda$startRobot$1(RobotBase.java:490)
at java.base/java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:840)
Also getting multiple
Warning at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.NamedCommands.getCommand(NamedCommands.java:65): PathPlanner attempted to create a command ‘Elevator First Pipe’ that has not been registered with NamedCommands.registerCommand
Your SwerveSubsystem construction looks different from the 2025 example YAGSL, which has SwerveSubsystem in a swervedrive subfolder.
Tried changing that unsuccessfully.
Recommend you update WPILIB and your vendor dependencies and make sure PathPlanner is the latest.

Then download the latest YAGSL example from GitHub - FRC-9438/Yagsl_2025, and test some simple NamedCommands like

NamedCommands.registerCommand("TestMe", Commands.runOnce(()->SmartDashboard.putNumber("AAAA",911)));.

Then copy over your swerve jsons, subsystems, commands etc.

You can see the errors if you run Simulation.
Add DriverStation.silenceJoystickConnectionWarning(true); to RobotContainer to filter the messages. Pathplanner docs are very specific about NamedCommands being before any other PathPlanner actions in your code.
The error message is telling you that something is happening with PathPlanner that it doesn’t like.
I’ve tried patching your code with what the new YAGSL example has without success.
Where did you get the way you are configuring the SwerveSubsystem?
